WEBVTT

00:08.095 --> 00:09.226
Previously on "All Rise"...

00:09.270 --> 00:10.662
Get off of me!

00:10.706 --> 00:11.620
I was stopped jogging
to work this morning.

00:11.663 --> 00:13.317
It's that kind
of blind justice

00:13.361 --> 00:15.232
that made me want to be
a judge in the first place.

00:15.276 --> 00:17.060
Detective Leyland did not
did not see Daphne in there

00:17.104 --> 00:19.541
committing that crime.That girl
participated in a crime.

00:19.584 --> 00:21.934
- You didn't have the evidence!
- Anything else, Your Honor?

00:21.978 --> 00:23.371
Either the District Attorney's
office thinks

00:23.414 --> 00:24.633
that the truth matters
or it doesn't.

00:24.676 --> 00:27.070
Not your monkey, Mark.I want the monkey!

00:27.114 --> 00:28.376
Show me the monkey!

00:28.419 --> 00:30.465
- Pay up.
- Why don't you take the $50

00:30.508 --> 00:32.162
out of the $200 you owe me
from the game last month?[ elevator bell dings ]

00:32.206 --> 00:34.338
On a court reporter's
salary?

00:34.382 --> 00:36.079
- Luke, are you okay?
- Actually, no.

00:36.123 --> 00:38.516
- You want to get out of here?
- Hell, yeah.

00:38.560 --> 00:41.389
♪♪♪

00:44.522 --> 00:46.524
[ men hooting and whistling ]

00:46.568 --> 00:48.135
- Take this suit, please.
- I got it, I got it.

00:48.178 --> 00:50.963
All right, all right.
That's enough.

00:51.007 --> 00:53.749
Dylan Frank.

00:53.792 --> 00:56.447
[ indistinct conversations ]

00:56.491 --> 00:59.189
[ police radio chatter ]

00:59.233 --> 01:00.364
[ door buzzes ]

01:00.408 --> 01:01.583
[ gate clanks ]

01:04.673 --> 01:08.633
Ms. Lopez,
what'd you bring me?[ handcuffs click ]

01:08.677 --> 01:11.158
Mariscos Jalisco.
Tacos de camarón.[ men hooting ]

01:11.201 --> 01:14.248
- Oh, my God.
- Best tacos in L.A.

01:14.291 --> 01:16.989
We need to get you changed.
Big day. Big field trip.

01:17.033 --> 01:19.992
[ men whistling and hooting ]

01:20.036 --> 01:22.430
[ door buzzes, clacks ]

01:22.473 --> 01:25.346
You want tacos,
you need to be nice.

01:25.389 --> 01:28.088
Which of these says
Sphinx-like judge?

01:28.131 --> 01:30.177
- You look good in heels.
- Not the point.

01:30.220 --> 01:32.657
Today I need gravitas
andagility.

01:32.701 --> 01:35.225
Jury view is a big swing.
Nervous?

01:35.269 --> 01:36.966
Excited. It's everything
I've worked for--

01:37.009 --> 01:38.707
fair trials, no excuses.

01:38.750 --> 01:41.013
Hmm. What happened
to taking it slow?

01:41.057 --> 01:43.146
You take it slow
with the Bureau?I pick my battles.

01:43.190 --> 01:44.974
You don't think
this is a good idea.

01:45.017 --> 01:46.280
I think if you think

01:46.323 --> 01:49.152
taking the entire trial
halfway across the city

01:49.196 --> 01:51.154
to the scene of the crime...
- Defendant's been charged

01:51.198 --> 01:52.851
with aiding and abetting
a murder.

01:52.895 --> 01:55.245
I granted the defense
jury view in the int--

01:55.289 --> 01:57.682
In the interest of justice.
I know. I hear you.

01:57.726 --> 02:02.296
This is how court should work--
active, engaged.Volatile.

02:02.339 --> 02:06.648
Not you. The juries. I prefer
to testify at bench trials

02:06.691 --> 02:09.346
so I can focus on the judge.
- It's the right thing to do.

02:11.087 --> 02:12.567
Permission to approach.

02:18.399 --> 02:20.096
Mm.

02:20.140 --> 02:21.576
When you want
to make a difference,

02:21.619 --> 02:24.492
you don't hold back,
and I love that.

02:24.535 --> 02:26.189
[ squeals ]

02:26.233 --> 02:27.973
[ giggles ]

02:28.017 --> 02:29.627
Can't be late.

02:29.671 --> 02:30.889
So I'll just
put all of this away.

02:30.933 --> 02:33.370
- Love you.
- I love you.

02:33.414 --> 02:35.155
Once we get to the club,
the jury gets off the bus,

02:35.198 --> 02:37.200
and we take them
to exactly where you said

02:37.244 --> 02:40.203
when the shooting happened.It's gonna look a lot different
during the day.

02:40.247 --> 02:41.596
It doesn't matter.
Dylan, it's not about

02:41.639 --> 02:42.640
what you saw.
It's about what you heard.

02:42.684 --> 02:44.599
Which was nothing.
I heard nothing.

02:44.642 --> 02:46.296
And the best way
to prove that to a jury

02:46.340 --> 02:47.645
is to have them
experience it for themselves.

02:47.689 --> 02:49.473
You didn't
aid and abet anything

02:49.517 --> 02:50.605
because you didn't hear
the gunshots.

02:50.648 --> 02:51.823
You didn't know
there was a murder.

02:51.867 --> 02:53.260
Chris was your friend,
but you didn't know

02:53.303 --> 02:55.044
what he was gonna do
that night.Sing it, sister.

02:55.087 --> 02:56.480
And remember, they're gonna
be watching you,

02:56.524 --> 02:59.179
so you have one job.
- Don't look like a thug.

02:59.222 --> 03:01.616
Mm-hmm. Be focused.
Be interested.

03:01.659 --> 03:03.139
If you look bored,
you look guilty.

03:03.183 --> 03:04.706
[ indistinct radio chatter ]

03:04.749 --> 03:06.838
Okay. [ sighs ]

03:06.882 --> 03:09.276
So? What you think?

03:09.319 --> 03:10.625
I've had better.

03:10.668 --> 03:12.627
Ricky's on Riverside
got the edge.

03:12.670 --> 03:14.281
- Uh, no way. No chance.
- Mm-hmm.

03:14.324 --> 03:16.413
- That is crazy talk.
- I'm serious.

03:16.457 --> 03:18.763
Prosecutor is gonna
try to paint you as a thug.

03:18.807 --> 03:20.896
- She's feeding their bias.
- Dylan's on the move.

03:20.939 --> 03:22.376
She wants the jury to see you
as a getaway driver.

03:22.419 --> 03:24.291
[ door buzzes ]Now it's my turn.

03:24.334 --> 03:25.683
Lola: A prison bus?

03:25.727 --> 03:27.381
That's what they had.
That's what we're taking.

03:27.424 --> 03:29.905
Box lunches are ordered.
Police are at the scene.

03:29.948 --> 03:32.386
- Oh, you are loving this.
- No, you're projecting.

03:32.429 --> 03:33.865
What happened to "creative"?

03:33.909 --> 03:35.476
The entire point
of a courtroom...

03:35.519 --> 03:36.999
"One of those
creative judges."

03:37.042 --> 03:38.870
...is that it isn't
the real world.

03:38.914 --> 03:40.655
It's sealed off
from the real world.

03:40.698 --> 03:43.310
You are notgoing
to ruin this for me.

03:43.353 --> 03:45.399
Emily:
That prosecutor won't win.

03:45.442 --> 03:46.704
When I'm done with that jury,

03:46.748 --> 03:47.966
they're gonna believe you,
not her.

03:48.010 --> 03:49.272
So I wear a suit

03:49.316 --> 03:51.361
and we emphasize my major
in urban policy?

03:51.405 --> 03:53.363
That's right.'Cause if I hadn't
finished high school,

03:53.407 --> 03:56.061
if I said "aksed"
instead of "asked,"

03:56.105 --> 03:58.325
we'd have a problem?
- Dylan, I will crush anything

03:58.368 --> 03:59.717
that gets in the way
of them seeing you.

03:59.761 --> 04:01.371
- Then put me on the stand.
- Not gonna happen.

04:01.415 --> 04:03.199
- You have a prior.
- I can explain to them--

04:03.243 --> 04:07.116
The DDA will have a field day.
Don't worry. I've got this.

04:07.159 --> 04:09.901
[ door buzzes and clacks ]She never quits.
You got lucky.

04:11.816 --> 04:14.558
Everybody needs a hat.
You are going to be in the sun.

04:14.602 --> 04:17.605
The bus is waiting.
This jury will not be late.

04:17.648 --> 04:20.390
Badges visible. Cellphones away!

04:20.434 --> 04:21.957
Thank you!

04:22.000 --> 04:24.264
[ indistinct radio chatter ]

04:26.309 --> 04:28.746
Mark: Great job
on the electronic surveillance

04:28.790 --> 04:30.095
of Mabbit, Detective Leyland.[ elevator bell dings ]

04:30.139 --> 04:31.445
Honest to God,
40 bucks on Amazon.

04:31.488 --> 04:32.881
The video was spectacular.

04:32.924 --> 04:34.491
Camera looks
like a phone charger.

04:34.535 --> 04:36.232
It isa phone charger.

04:36.276 --> 04:38.234
Even the audio is clear.
That never happens.

04:38.278 --> 04:40.149
I had an undercover
go in as a janitor.

04:40.192 --> 04:41.716
- Just plugged it in.
- And you got him.

04:41.759 --> 04:43.935
We got him.
Two years hard work.

04:43.979 --> 04:46.416
I'll land it.
First round's on me.

04:46.460 --> 04:49.332
Judge: Trevor Mabbit,
do you waive formal reading

04:49.376 --> 04:50.768
of the complaint
and statement of rights?

04:50.812 --> 04:52.117
- Yes, Your Honor.
- On the charge of possession

04:52.161 --> 04:54.729
for sales
of a controlled substance,

04:54.772 --> 04:56.948
how do you plead?
- Not guilty.

04:56.992 --> 04:58.472
Your Honor, Mr. Mabbit
is solely responsible

04:58.515 --> 04:59.951
for operations
at his auto parts business,

04:59.995 --> 05:01.170
a family man.
We request that he be--

05:01.213 --> 05:03.041
Trevor Mabbit runs

05:03.085 --> 05:04.434
a multimillion-dollar
heroin ring,

05:04.478 --> 05:06.306
a product that has killed
thousands.

05:06.349 --> 05:08.220
He uses violence
as a management tool...

05:08.264 --> 05:09.657
Your Honor--and has both the means
and the motive

05:09.700 --> 05:11.789
to flee the country.My client's not going anywhere.

05:11.833 --> 05:13.400
Thank you, Ms. Chavan,

05:13.443 --> 05:15.140
and, Mr. Callan,
you've made your point.

05:15.184 --> 05:18.666
Mr. Mabbit, bail is set
at $1.5 million.

05:18.709 --> 05:21.538
That should be sufficient
incentive to stick around.

05:21.582 --> 05:24.498
I assume you'll be bombarding
me with pre-trial motions.

05:24.541 --> 05:27.979
I'll see you in a few weeks.
Adjourned.

05:28.023 --> 05:29.285
[ gallery murmuring ]

05:29.329 --> 05:31.243
Already drafted
a motion to suppress.

05:31.287 --> 05:33.245
As soon as I get
that video surveillance kicked,

05:33.289 --> 05:36.597
your case falls apart.We're putting him away.

05:38.773 --> 05:40.209
Mabbit didn't know
what hit him.

05:40.252 --> 05:41.950
Lola: Nice. What about bail?

05:41.993 --> 05:45.083
$1.5. He's not going anywhere.
Whoo! I was in top form.

05:45.127 --> 05:46.737
And so modest.

05:46.781 --> 05:48.435
Yeah, well, killer evidence.[ telephone rings in distance ]

05:48.478 --> 05:50.393
You on the bus yet? Nah.

05:50.437 --> 05:52.830
Sherri won't let them
leave without me, I don't think.

05:52.874 --> 05:54.397
Who are you working with on this?

05:54.441 --> 05:56.225
Jackie Leyland, narcotics.

05:56.268 --> 05:58.445
How many times when we were
working together did we wish

05:58.488 --> 05:59.794
that we could bring a jury
to the scene of the crime?

05:59.837 --> 06:01.273
And now you have the power.

06:01.317 --> 06:02.927
I love it.Mark, you have to check
everything.

06:02.971 --> 06:04.189
What? Jackie Leyland?

06:04.233 --> 06:05.539
Yeah, we worked together

06:05.582 --> 06:06.844
on that string of robberies
in Van Nuys.

06:06.888 --> 06:08.803
Check the casework.
You have to check it.

06:08.846 --> 06:11.022
- What?
- Look, I can't go into details.

06:11.066 --> 06:12.763
Just do yourself a favor.

06:12.807 --> 06:15.331
- What am I looking for?
- Shortcuts.

06:15.375 --> 06:20.336
♪♪♪

06:20.380 --> 06:24.384
[ indistinct
police radio chatter ]

06:25.907 --> 06:27.082
[ siren wailing in distance ]I didn't think you'd
actually go through with it.

06:27.125 --> 06:29.301
- It's absurd.
- I need to impeach

06:29.345 --> 06:32.435
your discriminatory statements
about my client.Oh, you're calling me a racist?

06:32.479 --> 06:34.611
That's an outrageous claim
to make--You implied
his fraternity is a gang.

06:34.655 --> 06:35.873
Take it back,
or I'll withdraw

06:35.917 --> 06:37.614
the plea offer
I was about to make.

06:37.658 --> 06:39.616
We rejected your offer
twice.

06:39.660 --> 06:41.270
His only defense
is the testimony

06:41.313 --> 06:43.838
of a convicted murderer.
- My client is innocent,

06:43.881 --> 06:45.970
and your unconscionable
smear campaign

06:46.014 --> 06:49.452
is a disgrace.Ms. Lopez,
this is Mr. Frank's vehicle.

06:49.496 --> 06:54.196
A meat wagon? No.

06:54.239 --> 06:56.764
No, no, no, no, no, no.

06:56.807 --> 07:00.115
They gave you a prison bus.
Fantastic.

07:00.158 --> 07:01.638
Judge Benner, good morning.

07:01.682 --> 07:04.467
When was the last time
anyone did a jury view? O.J.?

07:04.511 --> 07:06.295
There have been
one or two since.

07:06.338 --> 07:08.471
Oh, I've had
defense lawyers ask.

07:08.515 --> 07:10.604
Never actually granted one.

07:10.647 --> 07:11.822
Gutsy move, Carmichael.

07:11.866 --> 07:14.172
I say
leave no stone unturned.

07:14.216 --> 07:15.870
Or Pandora's Box unopened.

07:15.913 --> 07:17.001
Your Honor.

07:17.045 --> 07:18.612
Wait, Your Honor.
Before we go--

07:18.655 --> 07:20.440
"Good morning,
Judge Carmichael"--

07:20.483 --> 07:22.180
That's the friendly way
to begin.

07:22.224 --> 07:23.965
- Good morning.
- Your Honor, good morning.

07:24.008 --> 07:27.011
It isa good morning.Good morning.
My client is being--

07:27.055 --> 07:29.100
Are we allowed?
Can we talk right now?

07:29.144 --> 07:30.406
I don't see why not.

07:30.450 --> 07:33.278
Uh, it's your party.

07:33.322 --> 07:34.497
Good luck.

07:35.542 --> 07:36.934
Speak.They're planning
on putting my client

07:36.978 --> 07:39.850
into a meat wagon.
- I had nothing to do with that.

07:39.894 --> 07:42.766
Another grossly
prejudicial move.I don't care about the car.
I'm not a racist.

07:42.810 --> 07:44.028
Stop speaking.

07:47.554 --> 07:50.948
Mr. Watkins, could you please
put the defendant in that car?

07:50.992 --> 07:53.081
- Yes, ma'am.
- Thank you, Your Honor.

07:53.124 --> 07:54.952
Your Honor,
if I could just say--

07:54.996 --> 07:57.259
Still not speaking.
Walking away.

07:57.302 --> 08:00.392
[ indistinct radio chatter ]

08:02.438 --> 08:04.527
- Mr. Frank.
- Your Honor.

08:04.571 --> 08:05.528
[ indistinct radio chatter ]

08:05.572 --> 08:07.530
- It's time.
- Come on.

08:07.574 --> 08:10.272
Single file!

08:10.315 --> 08:13.841
Form a line so I can
check you off the list.

08:13.884 --> 08:15.712
Do not discuss the case.

08:15.756 --> 08:18.149
No interaction
with the judge!

08:25.853 --> 08:27.898
Any final words,
Your Honor?

08:32.816 --> 08:36.516
We pursue the truth,
no matter where it leads us.

08:36.559 --> 08:40.824
This is the purest essence
of our judicial system.

08:40.868 --> 08:42.913
To paraphrase
Clarence Darrow,

08:42.957 --> 08:45.133
justice has nothing to do

08:45.176 --> 08:47.570
with what goes on
insidea courtroom.

08:47.614 --> 08:50.051
Justice
is what comes out.

08:53.054 --> 08:54.490
All aboard![ air brakes hiss ]

08:54.534 --> 09:01.845
♪♪♪

09:01.889 --> 09:05.066
Captioned by
Los Angeles Distribution
and Broadcasting, Inc.

09:08.156 --> 09:14.162
♪♪♪

09:14.205 --> 09:16.207
[ bus rattles, all gasp ]

09:16.251 --> 09:18.079
[ jurors murmuring ]

09:18.122 --> 09:21.604
[ indistinct conversations ]

09:21.648 --> 09:23.388
It's already a disaster.

09:23.432 --> 09:25.086
The box lunches
are skimpy.

09:25.129 --> 09:26.348
The air conditioning
is broken.

09:26.391 --> 09:28.916
And yet
justice is in the air.

09:28.959 --> 09:30.657
[ whispers ] So exciting.

09:34.182 --> 09:36.010
I count nine guilty,
three not guilty.

09:36.053 --> 09:37.664
You think I've got 3?
I'm thinking 10 and 2.

09:37.707 --> 09:41.493
Mnh-mnh. Scruffy guy,
mom pants, death metal.

09:41.537 --> 09:43.452
No way. Mom pants?

09:43.495 --> 09:44.758
She's got a tell.
She rubs her face.

09:44.801 --> 09:45.628
Trust me. I'm a poker queen.
This is my thing.

09:45.672 --> 09:47.761
I hope I have enough.

09:47.804 --> 09:49.589
Maggie Palmer did a number
on them.

09:49.632 --> 09:52.374
She said "urban decay"
27 times literally.

09:52.417 --> 09:54.202
I was making little ticks
on my notepad.Hmm. I still can't believe

09:54.245 --> 09:56.683
Judge Carmichael went
for a jury view.

09:56.726 --> 09:59.468
- I know. I love her.
- I love her.

09:59.511 --> 10:03.646
[ gasps ] Oh. I...left
an important thing

10:03.690 --> 10:06.127
in a place...
that is...not here.

10:09.391 --> 10:11.654
You told her
we went on a date.

10:11.698 --> 10:14.309
No. Was that--
That wasn't a date.

10:14.352 --> 10:15.745
I'm calling it a date,
but I don't have to.

10:15.789 --> 10:18.139
That wasn't a datedate.

10:18.182 --> 10:20.141
It was a spontaneous,
impromptu,

10:20.184 --> 10:22.099
spur-of-the-moment...thing.

10:22.143 --> 10:24.624
Mm-hmm. Okay.

10:25.842 --> 10:28.845
- You nervous?
- No. No.

10:28.889 --> 10:30.542
This will work.

10:30.586 --> 10:32.675
So I know you're a pro,
and I'm still trying to decide

10:32.719 --> 10:34.546
what kind of lawyer
I want to be.

10:34.590 --> 10:35.939
As a public defender,

10:35.983 --> 10:38.376
you provide
the best defense always.

10:38.420 --> 10:40.596
I know that.
I've watched you.

10:40.640 --> 10:42.380
Does it make a difference
when you know they're innocent?

10:44.121 --> 10:46.080
I'm not sure I can be
a public defender because

10:46.123 --> 10:48.082
if the jury gets it wrong,
how do you recover from that?

10:50.954 --> 10:52.608
You don't.

11:00.181 --> 11:01.748
Is that all of it?

11:01.791 --> 11:03.445
Thing of beauty.

11:03.488 --> 11:04.968
I've seen this already.

11:05.012 --> 11:07.014
Just reminding you
how good it is.

11:07.057 --> 11:08.711
You wanted
a high profile case--

11:08.755 --> 11:10.147
I'm not saying
there's a problem.

11:10.191 --> 11:12.715
Callan.Our entire case
rests on this footage,

11:12.759 --> 11:14.891
and I've been told
that Leyland cuts corners.

11:14.935 --> 11:16.980
- Told by whom?
- I can't say.

11:17.024 --> 11:20.027
- Yeah, you can.
- No, I can't.

11:20.070 --> 11:21.681
Ifthere's a pattern
of misconduct--

11:21.724 --> 11:23.857
You sound
like a defense attorney.

11:23.900 --> 11:25.772
I need your sign-off
before I turn over rocks.We rely on the police daily.

11:25.815 --> 11:27.948
We start questioning
every piece of evidence,

11:27.991 --> 11:30.472
that trust is destroyed.
- I'm talking about one cop.

11:30.515 --> 11:32.213
Go after one cop, they think
you're going after all of 'em.

11:32.256 --> 11:34.781
We want Mabbit.
He is the worst of them.

11:34.824 --> 11:36.565
The police needed a warrant
to get this footage.

11:36.608 --> 11:37.871
The warrant is based
on information

11:37.914 --> 11:39.481
from a confidential
informant.

11:39.524 --> 11:42.266
I want our case to be sound.
I just...

11:42.310 --> 11:43.964
I just want to be sure.

11:44.007 --> 11:46.880
[ telephone rings in distance ]

11:46.923 --> 11:49.404
Okay, go.
Go see what's real.

11:51.754 --> 11:53.625
Man:
How do you open this window?

11:53.669 --> 11:57.194
- [ grunts ]
- Man: It's hot in here.

11:58.543 --> 12:00.458
Everything okay, Your Honor?

12:00.502 --> 12:02.547
I'm good.

12:02.591 --> 12:04.767
Have a seat, Mr. Watkins.

12:04.811 --> 12:06.116
We are gonna talk
about your future.

12:06.160 --> 12:07.901
Really?

12:07.944 --> 12:09.859
What are your plans
after the Bar?

12:09.903 --> 12:11.687
- Assuming I pass?
- You'll pass.

12:11.731 --> 12:14.255
And then...prosecutor?
You've seen a lot of trials.

12:14.298 --> 12:17.127
Well, I don't know.
Felony court's no joke.

12:17.171 --> 12:18.520
California tax code's
looking okay.

12:18.563 --> 12:19.826
Ugh.

12:19.869 --> 12:20.914
- Wills and estates?
- Gross.

12:20.957 --> 12:22.872
- Corporate acquisitions.
- Stop.

12:25.048 --> 12:26.528
My family--

12:26.571 --> 12:28.486
fight-the-power
kind of people.

12:28.530 --> 12:31.402
Didn't go over so well
when I became a prosecutor.

12:31.446 --> 12:34.623
"Get folk out.
Don't put 'em in."

12:34.666 --> 12:37.147
But the DA's office
gets to decide

12:37.191 --> 12:39.280
who gets charged
and with what.

12:39.323 --> 12:42.500
There's authority there
and responsibility.

12:42.544 --> 12:44.764
If you want to set
the terms of the fight,

12:44.807 --> 12:46.417
that's where you go.

12:46.461 --> 12:48.463
Hmm.

12:48.506 --> 12:51.292
[ Captain Planet and La Yegros'
"Que Quiero Volver"playing ]

12:51.335 --> 12:53.076
♪ Me sumerjo en la nada

12:53.120 --> 12:55.339
♪ Arrastrada entro yo

12:55.383 --> 12:57.820
♪ En cuclillas en la arena

12:57.864 --> 13:00.170
♪ A la orilla raspa el sol

13:00.214 --> 13:02.433
♪ Aliviando mi camino

13:02.477 --> 13:05.349
♪ Yo respiro, yo respiro

13:05.393 --> 13:07.656
♪ Cada huella que despido

13:07.699 --> 13:09.701
♪ Va marcando mi destino

13:09.745 --> 13:10.702
♪ Ay...

13:10.746 --> 13:12.226
Keep it orderly.

13:12.269 --> 13:14.794
There is shade for you
under the bridge. Find it.

13:14.837 --> 13:19.537
♪ Ay, que no puedo ver♪

13:19.581 --> 13:24.194
♪ Ay, tomaría un tren a casa ♪

13:24.238 --> 13:28.851
♪ Ay, que quiero volver

13:28.895 --> 13:31.636
[ indistinct conversations ]

13:36.250 --> 13:38.382
Detective.
Thanks for making the time.

13:38.426 --> 13:40.167
Always have time
for you, Callan.

13:40.210 --> 13:41.864
Just want to talk
through a couple of--

13:41.908 --> 13:43.866
Mabbit's lawyer,
Priya Chavan,

13:43.910 --> 13:45.563
she is a pit bull.
- Mm-hmm.

13:45.607 --> 13:48.871
She keeps going after
that video.

13:48.915 --> 13:50.917
So I'm just looking
at the warrant.

13:50.960 --> 13:53.354
What about the warrant?Confidential informant got you--

13:53.397 --> 13:56.139
usprobable cause.

13:56.183 --> 13:58.185
Yeah, I should probably
sit down with your guy.

13:58.228 --> 13:59.882
I just want to be ready.

13:59.926 --> 14:01.753
When did you get
so thorough?

14:01.797 --> 14:04.539
Let's bring him in.
No surprises.

14:04.582 --> 14:07.585
I promised him
no lawyers.

14:07.629 --> 14:09.892
Still...You I.D. my informant,
it's done.

14:09.936 --> 14:11.763
- No more intel.
- Mabbit's worth it.

14:11.807 --> 14:14.244
You want me to burn my CI
because you need to be ready?

14:14.288 --> 14:16.681
No, because Trevor Mabbit
needs to be shut down

14:16.725 --> 14:18.727
'cause I don't want
his heroin on the streets

14:18.770 --> 14:21.469
killing kids,
wrecking families. Don't you?

14:23.079 --> 14:25.821
I do. Good to know
we're on the same page.

14:25.865 --> 14:32.262
♪♪♪

14:32.306 --> 14:38.051
[ police radio chatter ]

14:38.094 --> 14:39.835
[ indistinct conversations ]

14:39.879 --> 14:42.011
Sherri:
That's it. Right there.

14:42.055 --> 14:43.926
Quickly, come on. Quick, quick.

14:43.970 --> 14:45.797
[ radio chatter continues ]

14:45.841 --> 14:48.931
Sherri: All right.
Grab a water. Pass it down.

14:48.975 --> 14:51.194
Here you go.

14:51.238 --> 14:54.197
[ indistinct conversations ]Everyone, come around the car.

14:54.241 --> 14:56.069
Quickly. Take your positions.

14:56.112 --> 14:58.114
[ indistinct conversations
continue ]

14:58.158 --> 15:00.029
Remember, you're engaged,
confident, focused.

15:00.073 --> 15:01.596
Focused. I got it.

15:04.251 --> 15:05.817
Jury keeps
sneaking looks at me

15:05.861 --> 15:08.733
like I'm gonna do something.Don't worry about it.

15:08.777 --> 15:12.650
I got this voice in my head,
like, am I standing innocent?

15:12.694 --> 15:14.870
Does an innocent person
cross his arms?

15:14.914 --> 15:17.568
You're doing great. Luke?

15:17.612 --> 15:19.222
Yeah. We're good.
We're almost there.

15:22.617 --> 15:25.098
[ clicking ]

15:25.141 --> 15:28.057
- Are we all good, Sara?
- Yes, Your Honor.

15:28.101 --> 15:30.451
This is seriously awesome.

15:30.494 --> 15:31.974
All right,
let's get this over with.

15:32.018 --> 15:34.281
We are now on the record.

15:34.324 --> 15:38.850
Everyone, we are here today
for a specific purpose.

15:38.894 --> 15:41.375
We are recreating
to the best of our ability,

15:41.418 --> 15:44.160
one, where exactly
Mr. Frank was standing

15:44.204 --> 15:45.988
when the shooting took place
in the alley,

15:46.032 --> 15:49.731
two, the ambient noise level
while Mr. Frank waited,

15:49.774 --> 15:53.691
three, if you individually
can hear any gunshots.

15:53.735 --> 15:55.911
Ms. Lopez.

15:58.348 --> 16:01.003
We know that Dylan pulled up
in his car with Chris Sims

16:01.047 --> 16:02.570
at 11:28 p.m.

16:02.613 --> 16:05.007
It was caught and time-stamped
by that security camera,

16:05.051 --> 16:08.097
previously introduced
as Defendant's Exhibit 1.

16:08.141 --> 16:10.099
Mr. Sims walked away
from the car

16:10.143 --> 16:12.145
while Dylan waited
inside the car.

16:12.188 --> 16:13.668
The police report says

16:13.711 --> 16:15.409
that Dylan told them
that the music was loud--

16:15.452 --> 16:17.411
so loud,
Dylan told the investigator,

16:17.454 --> 16:19.369
that he could not hear gunshots.

16:19.413 --> 16:20.805
The DJ in the club that night

16:20.849 --> 16:22.633
has provided
a specific volume setting

16:22.677 --> 16:24.374
to which the People and I
have stipulated.

16:24.418 --> 16:26.681
An officer is standing by
with blanks

16:26.724 --> 16:29.205
matching the caliber
of the weapon used.

16:29.249 --> 16:30.859
Your Honor, we're ready.

16:32.382 --> 16:33.905
Start the music.

16:33.949 --> 16:36.865
[ loud electronic dance music
playing ]

16:36.908 --> 16:42.262
♪♪♪

16:42.262 --> 16:46.918
♪♪♪

17:04.240 --> 17:07.678
[ music stops ]Your Honor, for the record,
10 seconds ago,

17:07.722 --> 17:10.507
an officer standing
in the same spot

17:10.551 --> 17:12.031
where the murder victim
was found

17:12.074 --> 17:13.641
fired two gunshots.

17:13.684 --> 17:16.078
[ murmuring ]

17:16.122 --> 17:18.080
This concludes
our successful demonstration.

17:18.124 --> 17:19.603
- Objection.
- Thank you, Counsel.

17:19.647 --> 17:21.997
I will rephrase.
Our demonstration is concluded.

17:22.041 --> 17:23.999
- Anything further, Ms. Lopez?
- No, Your Honor.

17:24.043 --> 17:25.479
Ms. Palmer,
anything to add?

17:25.522 --> 17:27.133
No, not at this time,
Your Honor.

17:27.176 --> 17:30.179
Okay, I think we're good.
We are adjourned.

17:30.223 --> 17:32.703
[ helicopter whirring overhead,
siren wailing in distance ]

17:32.747 --> 17:37.056
[ police radio chatter ]

17:37.099 --> 17:38.535
[ whispers indistinctly ]

17:38.579 --> 17:41.234
- Something's going on.
- Ladies and gentlemen,

17:41.277 --> 17:43.279
we have reports of
an active shooter in the area.

17:43.323 --> 17:45.194
We need to clear the street
right now.

17:45.238 --> 17:47.327
Let's go!Okay, let's keep calm,
everyone.

17:47.370 --> 17:50.286
Back on the bus.
Let's go. Move, move!

17:50.330 --> 17:51.418
[ indistinct conversations ]

17:51.461 --> 17:52.897
Male officer:
Let's go! Let's go!

17:52.941 --> 17:54.203
- Go!
- Female officer: Keep moving!

17:54.247 --> 17:55.900
Your Honor.

17:55.944 --> 17:57.511
[ sirens wailing ]Let's go!

17:57.554 --> 18:01.123
[ wailing continues,
tires screech ]

18:01.167 --> 18:02.864
We need to take cover right now!Your Honor, we need
to get you back inside.

18:02.907 --> 18:06.389
- In the building?
- This way! Hurry up! This way!

18:06.433 --> 18:08.609
- Move, move, move!
- Come on, people!

18:08.652 --> 18:10.176
Male officer: Go this way!

18:10.219 --> 18:12.656
[ sirens continue wailing ]Hurry up!

18:12.700 --> 18:15.311
[ indistinct conversations ]

18:15.355 --> 18:22.101
[ sirens continue wailing ]

18:27.106 --> 18:30.326
[ police radio chatter ]

18:30.370 --> 18:31.849
[ helicopter whirring nearby ]

18:31.893 --> 18:35.897
This is so not awesome.

18:35.940 --> 18:38.900
It's okay. We're okay.

18:40.206 --> 18:43.034
I shouldn't have let you do
this. That was my first mistake.

18:43.078 --> 18:44.993
You do know
I am your boss, right?

18:45.036 --> 18:46.603
The root of all our problems.

18:46.647 --> 18:48.823
It would be so much better
if I were in charge.

18:48.866 --> 18:54.089
[ police radio chatter ]

18:54.133 --> 18:56.483
Everyone, listen up.

18:56.526 --> 18:59.138
We are gonna stay calm.

18:59.181 --> 19:00.748
We are safe here.

19:00.791 --> 19:03.490
We have police with us
and sheriffs.

19:03.533 --> 19:05.579
We're gonna do what they say,
follow their directions,

19:05.622 --> 19:07.189
and we are going to be fine.

19:07.233 --> 19:08.321
Okay?

19:08.364 --> 19:09.757
[ woman gasping ]

19:09.800 --> 19:11.106
[ murmuring indistinctly ]

19:14.196 --> 19:16.329
Hey.

19:16.372 --> 19:17.852
How are you doing?

19:17.895 --> 19:20.681
- Where do you live?
- In Silver Lake.

19:20.724 --> 19:22.509
Ooh.

19:22.552 --> 19:26.208
Good ice cream in Silver Lake.
Pazzo Gelato.

19:26.252 --> 19:27.949
Did he have something
to do with this?

19:32.562 --> 19:34.216
Who, Mr. Frank?

19:34.260 --> 19:35.478
Could that be
a friend of his out there?

19:35.522 --> 19:37.088
He--He told him
we'd be here?

19:39.221 --> 19:40.918
Your Honor.

19:45.096 --> 19:49.100
[ radio chatter continues ]

19:49.144 --> 19:50.493
Dylan: Now they're scared.

19:50.537 --> 19:52.756
They're not even trying
to hide it.

19:52.800 --> 19:56.369
Listen, it worked, okay?
The demonstration was--

19:56.412 --> 19:59.285
Do you think anyone's
going to remember after this?

20:00.851 --> 20:01.852
[ loud banging on door ]Jeez!

20:01.896 --> 20:03.202
Male officer: All clear!

20:04.377 --> 20:06.640
Okay.

20:06.683 --> 20:08.076
[ indistinct conversations ]

20:08.119 --> 20:09.469
[ man chuckles ]

20:09.512 --> 20:14.691
[ indistinct conversations
continue ]

20:14.735 --> 20:16.737
[ gate rattles ]

20:16.780 --> 20:19.218
Okay, people!

20:19.261 --> 20:20.784
[ under breath ] This is why
I don't go clubbing.

20:20.828 --> 20:24.266
[ loudly ]
Everybody, get back on the bus.

20:24.310 --> 20:25.485
[ indistinct conversations,
police radio chatter ]

20:25.528 --> 20:26.964
Woman: Let's go.

20:27.008 --> 20:29.053
Woman: That message is received. You are correct.

20:29.097 --> 20:31.186
Wait!

20:31.230 --> 20:36.017
Man: Hold up.What just happened had
nothing to do with us, okay?

20:36.060 --> 20:37.758
I need you all to remember
the demonstration,

20:37.801 --> 20:39.368
the evidence you heard.

20:39.412 --> 20:42.066
That is your sworn duty.
Understand?

20:43.981 --> 20:45.853
Woman: Yeah.

20:45.896 --> 20:47.463
[ jurors murmuring ]

20:49.335 --> 20:50.901
I'm not gonna like this,
am I?

20:50.945 --> 20:52.729
I reviewed
Leyland's collars.

20:52.773 --> 20:54.775
Found a sweetheart plea deal
two years ago.

20:54.818 --> 20:56.516
[ sighs ]Multiple priors.
Named Connor White.

20:56.559 --> 20:58.257
You are positive
this is her CI?

20:58.300 --> 20:59.606
Got to be.
I need to go talk to him.

20:59.649 --> 21:01.129
Nothing in his record
shows a link to Mabbit.

21:01.172 --> 21:02.565
And the CI's
how she got the warrant.

21:02.609 --> 21:04.741
Goes to the duty judge
middle of the night,

21:04.785 --> 21:07.222
avoiding lawyers.
Look who the judge was.

21:07.266 --> 21:09.311
Rogstad.

21:09.355 --> 21:10.878
Who of course redacted
the informant's name.

21:10.921 --> 21:13.141
It was 3 a.m.
He was probably hammered.

21:13.184 --> 21:15.186
If there's a problem
and the video gets thrown out--

21:15.230 --> 21:17.580
- I'm looking for another way.
- Something. Anything.

21:17.624 --> 21:21.323
I know. I'm trying.
But without it, Mabbit walks.

21:21.367 --> 21:23.586
[ sighs ]

21:24.979 --> 21:27.416
[ telephone rings in distance ]

21:27.460 --> 21:29.288
Go see the informant.

21:30.724 --> 21:32.465
Benner: Is everyone okay?

21:32.508 --> 21:34.249
There was a suspect in the area,
armed and dangerous.

21:34.293 --> 21:37.296
They locked us in the nightclub
until he was apprehended.

21:37.339 --> 21:39.559
How are youdoing?We were never
in any real danger.

21:39.602 --> 21:41.778
- Not what I'm asking.
- Ever had a nightmare so vivid

21:41.822 --> 21:43.954
you keep forgetting
it was just a dream?

21:43.998 --> 21:46.000
- Sure.
- Like thatis how I'm feeling.

21:46.043 --> 21:47.610
And the jury?

21:47.654 --> 21:49.917
When people are afraid,
their instincts kick in.

21:49.960 --> 21:52.398
If they transfer that fear
onto the accused...

21:52.441 --> 21:53.703
You're worried they're
going to be biased.

21:53.747 --> 21:55.314
I wouldn't underestimate
the jury's intelligence.

21:55.357 --> 21:58.099
I know something about bias,
Judge Benner, and fear.

21:58.142 --> 22:00.406
During our little lockdown,
juror number 7 asked

22:00.449 --> 22:02.886
if the accused had
something to do with it,

22:02.930 --> 22:04.410
were we being targeted?

22:04.453 --> 22:06.325
Oh, juror number 7's
got to go.

22:06.368 --> 22:08.457
She will. What worries me
are the others,

22:08.501 --> 22:10.372
what's going on
in their heads.

22:10.416 --> 22:13.941
That's...a good question.
You've got a choice--

22:13.984 --> 22:16.030
get things back on track
and finish your trial

22:16.073 --> 22:18.119
or pack it in
and send everyone home.

22:18.162 --> 22:19.990
It's your call.
You know why?

22:22.123 --> 22:23.429
Because I'm the judge.

22:23.472 --> 22:27.998
♪♪♪

22:28.042 --> 22:29.391
You got the wrong guy.

22:29.435 --> 22:31.350
I don't know
any Detective Leyland.

22:31.393 --> 22:33.352
She busted you 2 years ago
on May 10th.

22:33.395 --> 22:34.744
You were selling meth
to high school students

22:34.788 --> 22:36.137
at Central Tech.
- Doesn't ring a bell.

22:36.180 --> 22:37.747
No? Hell of a plea deal--
community service

22:37.791 --> 22:39.053
instead of eight years
in prison.

22:39.096 --> 22:41.664
- What did you trade for that?
- Go...away.

22:41.708 --> 22:43.231
Dumb muscle thinks
about swinging.

22:43.274 --> 22:45.886
Really dumb muscle swings.
What kind of stupid are you?

22:45.929 --> 22:49.368
[ indistinct conversations ]

22:49.411 --> 22:51.282
You signed this affidavit?

22:51.326 --> 22:52.849
Says you witnessed
Trevor Mabbit

22:52.893 --> 22:55.112
meeting two known suppliers
outside the gym he owns

22:55.156 --> 22:57.593
and taking them inside to talk.
- Sure, I remember a gym.

22:57.637 --> 22:59.639
- On Figueroa.
- Gym on Figueroa. That's right.

22:59.682 --> 23:01.728
Except that's not what you
said in the statement, Connor.

23:01.771 --> 23:04.557
It's auto parts on Glendale.

23:04.600 --> 23:07.386
I don't...get this.
What are you...

23:07.429 --> 23:09.213
Are you and Leyland
on the same team?

23:09.257 --> 23:11.433
We want the same thing,
yes.

23:11.477 --> 23:13.435
So when she tells me
"This is what you saw,"

23:13.479 --> 23:16.351
I say, "Okay, I saw that."

23:16.395 --> 23:18.658
Now you want I should
see something different,

23:18.701 --> 23:20.442
say something else?

23:20.486 --> 23:21.835
Just start talking.

23:21.878 --> 23:23.402
[ child cries in distance ]

23:23.445 --> 23:26.187
Jury's up there right now,
thinking,

23:26.230 --> 23:28.276
"This is what happens
around those people."

23:28.319 --> 23:30.191
- We don't know that.
- This ain't fair,

23:30.234 --> 23:31.932
this whole field trip madness.

23:31.975 --> 23:34.891
I'm going to prison for stuff
that has nothing to do with me.

23:49.428 --> 23:51.342
We need to put you
on the stand.

23:51.386 --> 23:52.779
But my record.

23:52.822 --> 23:54.607
We bring it up first,
neutralize it.

23:54.650 --> 23:56.652
It's a risk,
but we should take it.

23:56.696 --> 23:58.959
Now you got me scared.

23:59.002 --> 24:01.831
I know. It's...

24:01.875 --> 24:03.833
Things went sideways
out there.

24:03.877 --> 24:06.662
It is. It's scary.
But we need to get it back.

24:06.706 --> 24:08.969
Look, it shouldn't be a risk
to show them who you are.

24:09.012 --> 24:11.798
I know that. You know that.
If we don't take the chance,

24:11.841 --> 24:14.540
that prosecutor
gets to define you,

24:14.583 --> 24:16.629
and we cannot
let that happen.

24:16.672 --> 24:20.241
Now...let's talk about
what I'm gonna ask you.

24:20.284 --> 24:21.547
♪♪♪

24:28.075 --> 24:30.512
I can only dismiss a juror
for an objective reason

24:30.556 --> 24:32.558
like a prejudicial statement
or they're traumatized.

24:32.601 --> 24:33.907
If your gut says that--

24:33.950 --> 24:35.386
Doesn't matter.
I granted the jury view

24:35.430 --> 24:37.519
so the people wouldn't just
rely on their instincts.

24:37.563 --> 24:39.303
I can't turn around now
or remove someone

24:39.347 --> 24:40.957
just because my gut
says I should.

24:41.001 --> 24:42.959
- So you weed out what you can.
- And then hope--

24:43.003 --> 24:44.613
hope this whole thing
doesn't fall down

24:44.657 --> 24:47.137
around that young man's head.
How's yours?

24:47.181 --> 24:49.183
Hope? Thin.

24:49.226 --> 24:51.272
I could argue that Leyland
was acting in good faith.

24:51.315 --> 24:53.404
Delgado might allow it.

24:53.448 --> 24:55.842
- No, she won't.
- No, she won't.

24:55.885 --> 24:57.408
Any other lawyer
would wait

24:57.452 --> 24:58.671
and see if the evidence
got through.

24:58.714 --> 25:00.368
- Not any other good lawyer.
- Mabbit is--

25:00.411 --> 25:02.675
Yes, he is, but the man
still has rights.

25:02.718 --> 25:04.851
To hell with his rights.
There. I said it.

25:04.894 --> 25:07.331
It has been said out loud.

25:07.375 --> 25:09.551
That man in prison.
That is a right thing.

25:09.595 --> 25:10.770
That is a good thing.

25:10.813 --> 25:12.075
How many people
have said that before us

25:12.119 --> 25:13.686
and been wrong? Mark--

25:13.729 --> 25:15.122
I know. I know. I know that.

25:15.165 --> 25:16.689
I'm not gonna do it.
I just..

25:16.732 --> 25:18.255
[ sighs ]

25:18.299 --> 25:21.476
Man, I am not looking forward
to what comes next.

25:23.217 --> 25:24.566
Assistant Chief Healy
told me,

25:24.610 --> 25:26.350
if I ever had a problem
with one of his officers,

25:26.394 --> 25:28.614
to call him.
- A back channel.

25:28.657 --> 25:30.137
I may need one.

25:30.180 --> 25:33.575
Talk to Leyland first.
Then let me know.

25:33.619 --> 25:35.969
Uh, hey. What about me?

25:37.666 --> 25:39.363
You know I need to hear it.

25:39.407 --> 25:40.930
Go good.

25:43.106 --> 25:45.631
[ exhales deeply ]

25:45.674 --> 25:49.112
[ siren wailing in distance ]

25:49.156 --> 25:51.071
Callan,
you ambushed my CI?

25:51.114 --> 25:52.594
You weren't cooperating.

25:52.638 --> 25:55.249
- How'd you find him?
- It wasn't hard, Detective,

25:55.292 --> 25:56.772
and if I can find him,
the defense can, too.

25:56.816 --> 25:58.208
You could have
gotten him killed.

25:58.252 --> 26:00.341
We can protect him.
Does Connor even know Mabbit?

26:00.384 --> 26:01.821
I couldn't find
a single connection.

26:01.864 --> 26:04.519
- You saw the video.
- The problem was your warrant.

26:04.563 --> 26:06.477
Are you really
gonna sink this?Prove to me it's legit.

26:06.521 --> 26:09.002
You saw the warrant.Prove to me
that Connor isn't lying.

26:09.045 --> 26:11.178
Seriously, help me understand
what's going on here.

26:11.221 --> 26:13.049
Doesn't it matter to you that--

26:13.093 --> 26:15.225
You didn't have
probable cause.Mabbit is guilty.

26:15.269 --> 26:17.184
All you had was hearsay
that a deal was going down,

26:17.227 --> 26:19.099
and it killed you that you
couldn't be there for it.

26:19.142 --> 26:20.883
You sunk this, not me.

26:20.927 --> 26:23.103
When I do my job,
I don't take shortcuts.

26:24.887 --> 26:26.802
I just want to make sure
you're good.

26:26.846 --> 26:29.805
After everything that
happened yesterday, I'm just...

26:29.849 --> 26:31.807
talking to every juror
one-on-one.

26:31.851 --> 26:34.375
I'm good, Your Honor.

26:36.029 --> 26:37.900
I-I was scared, but...

26:37.944 --> 26:39.946
but I'm good now.

26:41.687 --> 26:43.819
You feel you're still able
to consider the evidence

26:43.863 --> 26:46.561
fairly and impartially,
according to the law?

26:46.605 --> 26:48.258
Uh, I kept thinking
what people would say

26:48.302 --> 26:49.782
if I got, you know...

26:49.825 --> 26:51.610
[ imitates machine gunfire ]

26:51.653 --> 26:55.265
My kids, you know, they'd be
devastated, obviously.

26:55.309 --> 26:59.792
Um...but my two ex-wives--
they'd throw a party.

27:05.145 --> 27:06.712
Thank you.

27:08.888 --> 27:10.803
I just want to make sure
you're good

27:10.846 --> 27:13.153
after what happened yesterday.

27:13.196 --> 27:15.416
I might not be good.

27:15.459 --> 27:16.809
Could you tell me why?

27:16.852 --> 27:20.334
I just...don't know
what to think anymore.

27:20.377 --> 27:25.034
I look at him,
at the accused, and I...

27:25.078 --> 27:26.688
I'm just not sure.

27:26.732 --> 27:28.429
I know it's difficult,

27:28.472 --> 27:30.213
but until I send you all off
to deliberate,

27:30.257 --> 27:33.260
not knowing is exactly
where you should be.

27:33.303 --> 27:35.131
Guilty or not guilty,

27:35.175 --> 27:38.178
Dylan Frank deserves
a fair and unbiasedhearing.

27:38.221 --> 27:40.049
Can you give him that?

27:45.272 --> 27:47.970
Counselors,
please approach the bench.

27:49.885 --> 27:51.800
You were both
in my chambers earlier.

27:51.844 --> 27:53.672
You heard me speak
to the jurors.

27:53.715 --> 27:55.978
I have released
juror 7 and juror 12.

27:56.022 --> 27:57.414
Alternates will be
taking their place.

27:57.458 --> 27:59.068
Emily:
How about juror number 11?

27:59.112 --> 28:01.636
- She remains.
- And we're out of alternates.

28:01.680 --> 28:05.031
Correct. One more,
and we do this all over again.

28:05.074 --> 28:08.469
If either of you have something
to say, now is the time.

28:08.512 --> 28:10.079
I'm good, Your Honor.
Let's do this.

28:12.560 --> 28:13.822
I'm...ready, Your Honor.

28:13.866 --> 28:15.694
Counsel, you may proceed.

28:17.913 --> 28:21.090
Defense calls Dylan Frank
to the stand.

28:21.134 --> 28:23.353
I have
a criminal record, yes.

28:23.397 --> 28:26.313
I was busted for vandalism.
I was 18.

28:26.356 --> 28:28.402
- What kind of...
- Just kid stuff.

28:28.445 --> 28:30.926
We took a park bench
and tossed it around, you know?

28:30.970 --> 28:32.580
- Was anybody hurt?
- Nah.

28:32.623 --> 28:33.842
I mean, I dropped it
on my own foot.

28:33.886 --> 28:35.583
Limped for a week.

28:35.626 --> 28:37.498
Serves me right.
I was so stupid.

28:38.804 --> 28:40.501
All right, Dylan,

28:40.544 --> 28:42.590
let's get back to the night
of the shooting.

28:42.633 --> 28:44.766
Tell us what you heard while
you were waiting for Chris.

28:44.810 --> 28:47.813
Nothing but music.
Car windows were buzzing.

28:47.856 --> 28:50.293
No gunshots, no nothing.

28:50.337 --> 28:52.948
Just as we saw yesterday
at the scene.

28:52.992 --> 28:53.949
Clearly,
you're telling the truth.

28:53.993 --> 28:55.472
Objection.

28:55.516 --> 28:56.952
Let's not editorialize,
Ms. Lopez.

28:56.996 --> 28:59.563
Dylan, what happened
when Chris returned to the car?

28:59.607 --> 29:01.478
He got in.
He said, "Let's go."

29:01.522 --> 29:02.958
Did you know
what he'd been doing?

29:03.002 --> 29:04.264
I knew he'd been
buying drugs.

29:04.307 --> 29:07.310
Did he tell you
about the shooting?No.

29:07.354 --> 29:10.574
Did Chris seem agitated,
upset?He did, yeah, really upset.

29:10.618 --> 29:12.446
Did you ask him
why he was upset?

29:12.489 --> 29:14.491
No, I-I thought I knew why.

29:14.535 --> 29:16.058
Me and Chris, we've been
friends my whole life.

29:16.102 --> 29:19.148
Your Honor, are we really
going to allow--I'll allow it.

29:21.107 --> 29:22.935
Friends from jump.

29:22.978 --> 29:25.546
I did kindergarten mat time
with him, you know?

29:25.589 --> 29:27.417
He's the guy that split
his lunches with me

29:27.461 --> 29:28.723
in seventh grade.

29:30.203 --> 29:33.380
That night, when he asked me
to drive him,

29:33.423 --> 29:36.862
I lost it, and we argued.

29:39.865 --> 29:42.432
He was upset because he was
disappointing me.

29:42.476 --> 29:44.695
Then why help him
get the drugs?

29:44.739 --> 29:47.655
When someone is drowning,
you don't swim away.

29:47.698 --> 29:51.093
You stay close.
That night, he was hurting.

29:51.137 --> 29:55.794
I thought that if...we could
just get through today,

29:55.837 --> 29:59.319
I would be able
to help him...tomorrow.

30:03.018 --> 30:05.934
- Nothing further, Your Honor.
- Your witness, Ms. Palmer.

30:05.978 --> 30:09.416
Sounds like you and Chris
did everything together.

30:09.459 --> 30:11.070
Yeah.

30:11.113 --> 30:12.462
Get arrested together,
go to jail together.

30:12.506 --> 30:14.900
Objection.Get to your question,
Ms. Palmer.

30:14.943 --> 30:17.772
Let's talk about
your self-described stupidity.

30:17.816 --> 30:19.818
- Objection.
- Withdrawn.

30:19.861 --> 30:23.082
Otherwise known to this court
as a felony conviction.

30:23.125 --> 30:25.214
You and Chris,
your close friend,

30:25.258 --> 30:26.999
you tossed around a bench.

30:27.042 --> 30:28.043
Correct.

30:28.087 --> 30:29.305
Tossed it through a window.

30:29.349 --> 30:31.220
Yeah, but it was--

30:31.264 --> 30:33.179
Yeah.

30:33.222 --> 30:35.268
- So it was a smash and grab.
- Objection. Argumentative.

30:35.311 --> 30:36.660
It was a store.
Clearly a robbery.

30:36.704 --> 30:37.618
- I'm not proud of it.
- Your Honor.

30:37.661 --> 30:39.098
Ms. Palmer, you know better.

30:39.141 --> 30:40.882
The jury will disregard anything

30:40.926 --> 30:44.146
other than the fact
of the vandalism conviction.

30:46.105 --> 30:50.196
So you are a student
at Cal State L.A.

30:50.239 --> 30:52.894
Your focus is urban policy?

30:52.938 --> 30:54.113
That's right.

30:54.156 --> 30:55.941
When did you last
attend class?

30:55.984 --> 30:59.379
I didn't have
the $5,000 bail.

30:59.422 --> 31:00.815
I've been in custody
since my arrest.

31:00.859 --> 31:04.601
You attended class until
your arrest?

31:04.645 --> 31:07.953
You haven't set foot on campus
in over six months.

31:07.996 --> 31:09.998
- Objection. Relevance.
- I had to drop out.

31:10.042 --> 31:12.696
You just lied to the court.
What else are you lying about?Lola: Ms. Palmer.

31:12.740 --> 31:13.697
- I did not lie!
- You don't care about Chris.

31:13.741 --> 31:15.525
In fact,
you clearly don't care

31:15.569 --> 31:16.613
about the man that he
shot and murdered.Lola: That is enough!

31:16.657 --> 31:18.180
You don't know me![ jurors gasp ]

31:18.224 --> 31:19.703
You don'tknow me!

31:21.792 --> 31:25.361
Mr. Frank,
there is no question pending.

31:25.405 --> 31:27.276
Please sit down.

31:27.320 --> 31:28.843
[ mouths words ]

31:35.197 --> 31:36.633
Strike from the record
everything

31:36.677 --> 31:38.374
after the defense's objection.

31:38.418 --> 31:40.811
The jury will disregard
the characterizations.

31:40.855 --> 31:42.509
Ms. Palmer, do you have

31:42.552 --> 31:43.771
an appropriate line
of questioning?

31:43.814 --> 31:46.382
Nothing further.

31:54.434 --> 31:55.914
Why'd you drop out?

31:55.957 --> 31:57.524
You were partway
through junior year.

31:57.567 --> 32:01.049
Work. Tuition is high.

32:01.093 --> 32:03.922
I'm saying I'm a student
as a promise to go back.

32:03.965 --> 32:07.055
- To who?
- To me.

32:13.409 --> 32:15.629
It is your duty
to talk with one another

32:15.672 --> 32:18.110
and to keep an open mind,
and when you're in agreement,

32:18.153 --> 32:20.721
you'll come back in here
and deliver your verdict.

32:22.027 --> 32:25.334
- Bailiff.
- Right this way.

32:33.516 --> 32:35.388
[ knock on door, door opens ]

32:35.431 --> 32:37.129
Bailiff Watkins informs me

32:37.172 --> 32:39.000
the jury wants to go home
for the night.

32:39.044 --> 32:40.959
You need to remind them--Not to discuss the case
at home.

32:41.002 --> 32:43.222
I'll be in in a minute.

32:45.398 --> 32:47.574
When I was little,
maybe 5,

32:47.617 --> 32:49.880
my mom took me
to a protest rally--

32:49.924 --> 32:51.752
housing discrimination.

32:51.795 --> 32:53.232
Wasn't huge,
couple hundred people,

32:53.275 --> 32:55.451
big enough to get lost in.

32:55.495 --> 32:57.801
- She lost you?
- Or I wandered off.

32:57.845 --> 33:01.980
My dad went looking,
and she just waited,

33:02.023 --> 33:04.983
not moving
until the crowd thinned,

33:05.026 --> 33:07.115
and I came wandering back.

33:07.159 --> 33:08.987
She must have been terrified.

33:09.030 --> 33:11.598
I think I get
how she felt...

33:11.641 --> 33:13.556
waiting.

33:13.600 --> 33:15.994
If what happened yesterday

33:16.037 --> 33:19.475
is the reason
they convict Dylan Frank,

33:19.519 --> 33:23.305
this will--it will follow him
the rest of his life.

33:23.349 --> 33:24.915
Your Honor--

33:24.959 --> 33:27.048
It's so easy to put
your finger on the scale,

33:27.092 --> 33:28.615
you don't even notice
you're doing it.

33:28.658 --> 33:30.878
I didn't see that,
Your Honor.

33:30.921 --> 33:32.880
And if I did,
I would have told you...

33:32.923 --> 33:34.360
loudly.

33:34.403 --> 33:36.579
[ chuckles ]

33:41.802 --> 33:43.804
Let Luke know
I'll be right in.

33:54.119 --> 33:55.685
[ door closes ]

33:55.729 --> 33:57.339
[ exhales deeply ]

34:05.217 --> 34:06.827
[ switch clicks ]

34:11.310 --> 34:14.443
♪♪♪

34:14.487 --> 34:15.966
Appreciate your coming in.

34:16.010 --> 34:18.099
I'm sure we can get this
cleared up.

34:18.143 --> 34:22.016
[ indistinct conversations ]

34:22.060 --> 34:24.062
[ telephone ringing
in distance ]

34:25.976 --> 34:27.065
Detective.

34:30.981 --> 34:32.766
[ ringing continues ]

34:35.029 --> 34:37.945
Detective Leyland.
This is obviously a major case.

34:37.988 --> 34:39.120
We all want
to get it right.

34:39.164 --> 34:40.556
We're relying on you

34:40.600 --> 34:42.080
to get us into the end zone,
get that conviction.

34:42.123 --> 34:43.820
As you say, Counselor,
Trevor Mabbit's a big fish.

34:43.864 --> 34:45.953
Chief Healy,
you're aware of the nature

34:45.996 --> 34:47.737
of Detective Leyland's
investigation.

34:47.781 --> 34:49.870
I've been briefed.Sir, our whole case relies
on video surveillance,

34:49.913 --> 34:52.177
which in turn relies
on a search warrant.

34:52.220 --> 34:53.656
Gentlemen, I appreciate your
rigor, but Detective Leyland--

34:53.700 --> 34:55.615
Sir, I've just taken
Connor White's statement,

34:55.658 --> 34:57.573
her CI? He told me that--
- You spoke to him?

34:57.617 --> 35:00.533
He's in my office
right now.

35:00.576 --> 35:02.448
Were you aware of this?

35:02.491 --> 35:04.276
He lied, sir. The affidavit,

35:04.319 --> 35:06.191
the one that got you
your surveillance--

35:06.234 --> 35:07.931
it was fiction.

35:07.975 --> 35:10.499
Cold feet. He's frightened of
Mabbit. He's changing his story.

35:10.543 --> 35:12.675
Possibly. It's also possible
Detective Leyland

35:12.719 --> 35:15.200
didn't know
she was being lied to.

35:15.243 --> 35:18.028
In any case, the defense will
come after the evidence hard.

35:18.072 --> 35:19.378
If we're gonna win
those battles,

35:19.421 --> 35:21.815
we need to have confidence.
- In what?

35:24.296 --> 35:26.907
In Detective Leyland.

35:26.950 --> 35:28.909
We'd like to look
into her other case work,

35:28.952 --> 35:30.476
previous convictions.

35:30.519 --> 35:31.955
That's a lot of unpacking.

35:31.999 --> 35:33.087
We'll take it through
the courts if need be.

35:33.131 --> 35:34.306
Sir.

35:37.526 --> 35:41.095
I need to call the union
and my lawyer.

35:41.139 --> 35:43.489
[ sighs ]

35:46.579 --> 35:49.712
Give us the room, Detective.
Wait for me outside.

35:58.808 --> 36:01.159
If the surveillance is out,
do we have a case?

36:01.202 --> 36:02.682
No. Mabbit walks.

36:04.423 --> 36:06.338
I'll deal with this internally.

36:06.381 --> 36:08.470
Of course.

36:08.514 --> 36:09.993
It starts with desk duty,
pending an investigation.

36:10.037 --> 36:12.996
Then, if we find even a whiff
of anything improper,

36:13.040 --> 36:15.999
Leyland will be gone.
You got my word.

36:25.705 --> 36:26.967
[ police radio chatter ]

36:27.010 --> 36:28.708
I'm gonna puke.

36:28.751 --> 36:29.839
You're doing great,
youngblood.

36:29.883 --> 36:31.101
Luke's the expert.

36:31.145 --> 36:32.451
I've sat here with,
like, a hundred people

36:32.494 --> 36:34.061
waiting for verdicts.
This is the hardest part.

36:34.104 --> 36:37.064
I'm so sorry I didn't
tell you about school.

36:37.107 --> 36:40.198
It's okay. We're good.

36:40.241 --> 36:44.550
So you're studying, uh,
urban planning, right?

36:44.593 --> 36:47.727
- Yeah, when I go back.
- You like it?

36:47.770 --> 36:50.817
I started in art history.
Don't ask.

36:54.255 --> 36:59.042
I was up on Bee Rock
in Griffith Park.

36:59.086 --> 37:00.740
I hate heights.

37:00.783 --> 37:03.699
I was trying
to impress a girl.

37:03.743 --> 37:07.312
Standing on this rock,
knees shaking,

37:07.355 --> 37:09.139
looking at the city.

37:09.183 --> 37:12.708
It hit me--
somebody planned this.

37:12.752 --> 37:14.362
Well,
a lot of somebodies.

37:14.406 --> 37:18.975
Sure. But it was designed,
you know--

37:19.019 --> 37:21.674
the neighborhoods,
the highways,

37:21.717 --> 37:25.417
zoning laws,
all made for a purpose.

37:25.460 --> 37:26.896
So...

37:26.940 --> 37:28.768
I started studying,

37:28.811 --> 37:31.074
you know, reverse engineering
the designers' secrets

37:31.118 --> 37:32.946
from what got made--

37:32.989 --> 37:36.776
you know, what they love,
what they feared.

37:36.819 --> 37:38.343
It ain't pretty.

37:38.386 --> 37:41.084
Every shining city's built
on something pretty dark,

37:41.128 --> 37:44.174
but I don't think
it has to be.

37:44.218 --> 37:46.307
That's what I love--

37:46.351 --> 37:49.441
thinking about
where people and geography

37:49.484 --> 37:52.400
and buildings and laws
all intersect.

37:52.444 --> 37:53.575
Like a courthouse.

37:53.619 --> 37:55.011
- Yeah, I was gonna say.
- Yeah, exactly.

37:55.055 --> 37:56.752
Designed for a purpose.

37:56.796 --> 37:58.319
Judges have their own
elevators.

37:58.363 --> 38:00.234
Prisoners come in
through the basement.

38:01.888 --> 38:03.455
Exactly.

38:03.498 --> 38:05.457
Tells you everything
you need to know

38:05.500 --> 38:08.068
about the purpose
of this building.

38:09.417 --> 38:11.158
Dylan?

38:11.201 --> 38:12.725
Sometimes when people
come in through the basement,

38:12.768 --> 38:15.118
they walk out
through the front door.

38:15.162 --> 38:17.686
[ cellphones chime ]

38:17.730 --> 38:19.601
They're back.

38:28.262 --> 38:30.351
Is that the motion
to dismiss?

38:30.395 --> 38:33.441
Yep. There goes my invite
to the policeman's ball.

38:33.485 --> 38:35.313
- Callan.
- Cops don't forget, Choi,

38:35.356 --> 38:36.705
not even our own office.

38:36.749 --> 38:38.925
Doubt and side eye.

38:38.968 --> 38:40.796
And all of a sudden,
I'm the bad guy.

38:40.840 --> 38:43.930
Hwy, slow down, Callan.
His lawyer--what's her name?

38:43.973 --> 38:45.453
Priya Chavan.
Spectacular name.

38:45.497 --> 38:46.976
She would have found
the CI.

38:47.020 --> 38:49.196
And when she blew up the case
in court for all to see,

38:49.239 --> 38:51.154
it would have meant long-term
damage for our office.

38:51.198 --> 38:52.982
You saved our ass.

38:53.026 --> 38:54.680
That's not the way
it's gonna look.I don't care.

38:54.723 --> 38:56.638
The job is to seek justice,
not convictions.

38:56.682 --> 39:00.033
That is what you are sworn
to do, and that is what you did.

39:00.076 --> 39:03.863
Justice prevailed.
Proud of you.

39:03.906 --> 39:05.647
Proud of what you did
with this case.

39:05.691 --> 39:07.606
We'll get Mabbit another way.

39:07.649 --> 39:10.043
[ elevator bell dings ]

39:10.086 --> 39:11.827
Has the jury reached a verdict?

39:13.786 --> 39:15.483
We have, Your Honor.

39:17.224 --> 39:21.315
Foreperson, please hand
the verdict form to the bailiff.

39:30.716 --> 39:39.812
♪♪♪

39:44.947 --> 39:46.645
Go ahead.

39:46.688 --> 39:48.908
"As for the charge of murder
in the second degree,

39:48.951 --> 39:51.563
"in violation of Penal Code
Section 187 Subdivision 'A',

39:51.606 --> 39:54.043
"we the jury find the defendant

39:54.087 --> 39:56.785
not guilty."
- [ exhales deeply ]

40:01.834 --> 40:03.966
Would you like to have
the jury polled, Counselor?

40:04.010 --> 40:05.490
Palmer: No, Your Honor,
that won't be necessary.

40:05.533 --> 40:07.709
With the court
having accepted, received,

40:07.753 --> 40:10.364
and ordered filed
your verdicts in this case,

40:10.408 --> 40:12.497
your duty as jurors
is now complete.

40:12.540 --> 40:13.802
Thank you.

40:13.846 --> 40:17.458
Mr. Frank...you're free to go.

40:24.422 --> 40:28.338
[ sniffles ]

40:35.824 --> 40:38.348
[ jurors murmuring ]

40:38.392 --> 40:40.873
[ exhales deeply ]

40:45.878 --> 40:47.096
[ door closes ]

40:47.140 --> 40:48.881
I miss this courtroom.

40:48.924 --> 40:50.796
I hardly ever get
to work here anymore.

40:50.839 --> 40:52.580
- That's my fault.
- It's ridiculous.

40:52.624 --> 40:54.016
I worried you'd favor me?

40:54.060 --> 40:55.496
You'd never admit
I won an argument.

40:55.540 --> 40:57.455
That's because
you've never won.Hmm.

40:57.498 --> 41:00.066
You can blame me if you want.
I knew about the detective,

41:00.109 --> 41:03.156
and I thought if I warned her...
- It's not on you.

41:03.199 --> 41:05.506
- I should trust my instincts.
- You dotrust your instincts.

41:05.550 --> 41:07.987
Youdid a jury view,
and it worked.

41:08.030 --> 41:09.902
Nearly cost a young man
his freedom.

41:09.945 --> 41:12.600
You don't believe in nearly.
It's guilty or not guilty.

41:12.644 --> 41:15.560
You had a good day.

41:15.603 --> 41:18.345
- What?
- Did you just win an argument?

41:18.388 --> 41:22.523
Oh, I love this room.
I do. I love it.

41:22.567 --> 41:24.090
Me, too.

41:24.133 --> 41:28.573
You, on the other hand,
had a horribleday.

41:28.616 --> 41:31.663
Shut up.Total disaster.
Bad guy walked.

41:31.706 --> 41:34.448
You are terrible at pep talks,
you know that?Mm.

41:36.711 --> 41:38.757
- I should get back.
- I know.

41:41.281 --> 41:44.719
Hey, maybe we can find
a place to have dinner

41:44.763 --> 41:47.069
